(a) Illustrative schematic of ZnO NWs in dark condition. The left drawing in (a) illustrates the schematic of energy band diagrams of ZnO NWs, showing band-bending and trap states. The right drawing shows oxygen molecules adsorbed at the surface of NWs that capture free electrons forming a low conductivity depletion layer near the surface. (b) Illustrative schematic of ZnO NWs in UV illumination condition. Photo-generated holes migrate to the surface and are trapped, while unpaired photo-generated electrons are pumped to a conducting band of ZnO contributing to the photocurrent. (c) Dye-sensitized mechanism. The left drawing in (c) illustrates an energy level under VIS illumination of ZnO/RhB hybrid system.

